				<div class="comment-body"><p>The photo of the 1970 Hugo Award you have posted here: <a href="../../index.html?page_id=104" rel="nofollow">http://www.thehugoawards.org/?page_id=104</a> is not the actual award that was presented in Germany in 1970.  Kelly Freas was unhappy with the appearance of the base on the trophy he received and had a new one specially made to replace it.  Kelly&#8217;s 1970 trophy, the one you have shown in the photo, is therefore unique.  For more background on this, I refer you to Mike Glyer&#8217;s article in Mimosa #14: <a href="http://www.jophan.org/mimosa/m14/glyer.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.jophan.org/mimosa/m14/glyer.htm</a></p>
</div>

