				<div class="comment-body"><p>Hi, I believe there is an error in your page explaining voting system for the 2nd to 5th place. You say: The method used by Hugo Administrators to determine 2nd through 5th place is to remove all of the votes that placed the winner first, and then repeat the counting process from the start. The winner of that second count will get second place.<br />
If this is the case, then for example in this year&#8217;s (2011) best novel, in order to get your 2nd winner, you have to remove all &#8220;first&#8221; votes of Blackout/All Clear, right? Still, the same number of votes as before placed Feed first, and that should be 416 and not 476.<br />
What I don&#8217;t get right?<br />
Thanks in advance!</p>
</div>

